```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int num = 1;

    while (num <= 5) {
        printf("%d\n", num);
        num++;
    }

    return 0;
}
```

In this example, the program will repeatedly print the values of `num` as long as `num` is less than or equal to 5. The loop starts with `num` initialized to 1, and with each iteration, it increments `num` by 1 and prints its value. The loop continues until `num` becomes 6, at which point the condition becomes false and the loop terminates.

